## Resolver Pattern

Route operations by a discriminant (usually `ChainKind`) through a typed `Record` map — never `switch`/`case`. Each resolver set handles one responsibility.

### File layout

```
<feature>/
  index.ts        — router: extract discriminant, select resolver, delegate
  resolver.ts     — resolver type + input/output types
  resolvers/      — one file per routing value
    evm.ts
    solana.ts
    ...
  chains.ts       — (optional) supported subset for validation
```

### Naming

- **Files** match the routing value: `evm.ts`, `utxo.ts`, `sui.ts`.
- **Functions** include the full operation + routing value: `getEvmCoinBalance`, `broadcastSolanaTx`, `getSuiTxHash`.

### Router patterns

**Route by ChainKind (full set):**

```ts
const resolvers: Record<ChainKind, SomeResolver<any>> = {
  evm: getEvmX,
  solana: getSolanaX,
  // ... all chain kinds
}

export const doX: SomeResolver = async input =>
  resolvers[getChainKind(input.chain)](input)
```

**Route a supported subset (validate with `isOneOf`):**

```ts
const resolvers: Record<SupportedKind, SomeResolver<any>> = {
  evm: getEvmX,
  solana: getSolanaX,
}

export const doX: SomeResolver = async input => {
  const chainKind = getChainKind(input.chain)
  if (!isOneOf(chainKind, supportedKinds)) {
    throw new Error(`Unsupported chain kind: ${chainKind}`)
  }
  return resolvers[chainKind](input)
}
```

### Resolver typing

```ts
import { Chain } from '@core/chain/Chain'
import { Resolver } from '@lib/utils/types/Resolver'

export type DoXInput<T extends Chain = Chain> = {
  chain: T
}

export type DoXResolver<T extends Chain = Chain> = Resolver<
  DoXInput<T>,
  Promise<OutputType>
>
```

### Existing resolver sets

Chain-based routing:
- `core/chain/coin/balance/` — coin balance by chain kind
- `core/chain/tx/hash/` — tx hash extraction
- `core/chain/tx/broadcast/` — tx broadcasting
- `core/chain/tx/status/` — tx status polling
- `core/chain/coin/token/metadata/` — token metadata (subset)
- `core/chain/coin/find/` — coin finder (subset)
- `core/mpc/keysign/fee/` — keysign fee estimation
- `core/mpc/keysign/signingInputs/` — signing input construction
- `core/mpc/keysign/chainSpecific/` — chain-specific keysign data
- `core/chain/security/blockaid/tx/validation/` — Blockaid validation (subset)
- `core/chain/security/blockaid/tx/simulation/` — Blockaid simulation (subset)

Non-chain routing:
- `core/inpage-provider/popup/` — routes by popup method
- `core/inpage-provider/background/` — routes by background method
